      "content": "i get the socioeconomic part, but i'm trying to be really thorough with my review. some people argue that even when you control for income and education, the disparities don't go away entirely. can you look into what the actual data says about those specific gaps? like, are there any studies that suggest there are more significant differences in certain types of crime across different racial demographics regardless of their wealth?",
